Generating codewords.
We use BCH coding algorithm to generate codewords. The BCH coding is chosen because it provides the codes with a wide range of the message and code lengths. The choice of the coding algorithm is, however, not crucial to our work and our method works with other ECC algorithms as well.
We generated codewords of lengths 127,255127255127,255 and 511511511, where the code lengths are chosen to be smaller than the number of users (1,00010001,000) to emulate the setting with a very large number of users. For each code length, we find the message length of greater than or equal to 646464 that produces a valid code. TableÂ 1 shows the code statistics.
